      "content": "Here's a draft of a candidate rejection email that balances professionalism and kindness:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the senior developer position at our Austin office. We were impressed by your technical skills and accomplishments during the interview process, and you truly stood out as a strong contender. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose background in distributed systems aligns more closely with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision is in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. We appreciate the time you took to interview with us and the effort you put into preparing for the process. We're confident that you'll find a great opportunity that aligns with your skills and experience.\n\nWe wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors and hope to have the chance to work with you again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nThis email aims to be professional and kind while still conveying that we've made a decision that aligns with our company's needs. Feel free to modify it to fit your tone and style.",
